listBibl.bibl:
Because of the excision of ten leaves from our manuscript, presumably on account of their decoration, there are gaps at ten points, here identified by reference to the nearest contemporary printed text, the editio princeps of Antoine Verard's edition (Paris, c.1495-6) of the Bible historiale (Chambers no. 13): fols. 19/20, from Mark 16: 9 marie magdalene de la quelle (edn. sig. HHHviirb/II) to Cy commence le premier prologue de leuuangile saint Mathieu leuuangeliste; 
                           fols. 20/ 21, from the table to Matthew comment ihesus gairi le me to Matthew 1: 2 iacob. Jacob engendra iudas (edn. sig. EEE1ra/5); fols. 80/81, from the prologue to John, Et de nathanael to John 1: 12 tre faiz filz de dieu (edn. sig LLLivvb/3); 
                           fols. 103/4 from the prologue to Romans une dampnacion aussi to Romans 1: 20 sont faittes et entendues (edn. sig. NNiiijva/ 40); fols. 123/4, from 1 Corinthians 16: 13, soft fait en charite (edn. sig. OOOviiivb/10) to 2 Corinthians 1: II 
                           nous que graces soient faittes (edn. sig. PPPirb/5); fols. 136/7, from Ephesians 6: 4, et en la correccion nostre (edn. sig. PPPviiivb/5) to Philippians 1: 12 de iustice par ihesu crist 
                           (edn. sig. QQQ1rb/24); fols. 138/9, from Philippians 4: 18 Iai toutes chores et habonde. Ie sui rem (edn. sig. QQQiiva/41) to Colossians 1: 27 
                           Voult descouurir les richesses (edn. sig. QQQiiira/47); fols. 142/3, from 1 Thessalonians 5: 27 les sains freres. La grace de nos (edn. QQQvva/ 41) to 1 Timothy, 1: 12 Je rens graces a celui (edn. sig. QQQvivb/21); 
                           fols. 146/7, from 2 Timothy 4: 3 a leurs plaisirs qui auront sourdes (edn. sig. RRR1rb/30) to Philemon 9 en charite que to soies (edn. sig. RRR2vb/9); 
                           fols. 190/191, from 1 John 5: 13 (edn. sig. VVVvrb/39), de dieu it na mye vie. Ce vous to Jude 3 freres treschiers iai mestier (edn. sig. VVVvira/ii).
